The paper focuses on the use of deep reinforcement learning for robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the importance of interpretability in decision-making processes, which is a topic commonly discussed in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning for representation learning and the testing on a MuJoCo-based model suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of a hierarchical approach for decision-making in a robotic system suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
